<section class="section-tight">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="prose reveal">
      <p>
        The Quiet Pen ("we," "us," or "our") helps people write wedding vows, speeches, letters,
        and related pieces. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and
        the choices you have. By using our workbook, services, or website, you agree to the
        practices described here.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact and account details</strong> you provide when reaching out, such as your name and email address.</li>
        <li><strong>Project details</strong> you share through our questionnaires or consultations — the stories, memories, and preferences that inform your writing.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information</strong>, processed securely by a third-party payment provider. We do not store full card numbers ourselves.</li>
        <li><strong>Basic usage data</strong>, such as pages visited, collected to understand how the site is used and improve it.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>
        We use your information to deliver the workbook or service you've requested, communicate
        with you about your project, process payment, and respond to inquiries. Project details
        you share — your stories, memories, and preferences — are used solely to write or edit your
        piece. We do not use your personal stories for marketing, publish them, or share them with
        anyone outside the writer assigned to your project, without your explicit permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
      <p>
        Everything you share with us as part of a writing project is treated as confidential. We
        do not sell personal information, and we do not reuse your story details for other clients
        or public examples.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep information</h2>
      <p>
        We retain project files for as long as reasonably needed to support revisions or answer
        follow-up questions, and no longer than necessary for that purpose. You can request
        deletion of your information at any time by contacting us.
      </p>

      <h2>Third parties</h2>
      <p>
        We rely on a small number of trusted third-party services — for example, payment
        processing and email delivery — to operate our business. These providers only receive the
        information necessary to perform their function and are not permitted to use it for their
        own purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information at any
        time. To make a request, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are intended for adults planning weddings, speeches, and similar milestones.
        We do not knowingly collect information from children under 16.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy occasionally to reflect changes in our practices. We'll update
        the date at the top of this page whenever we do.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy or your information can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.
      </p>
